author: Alan Fram, Associated Press
title: Abortion proponents complain after new videos posted online
text: Photo: Jacquelyn Martin, AP FILE - In this Oct. 8, 2015, file photo, Rep. Jason Chaffetz, R-Utah, smiles while speaking to the media on Capitol Hill in Washington. A trade group for abortion providers is asking Chaffetz to investigate after secretly recorded videos were posted online by a conservative blogger who wrote that he got the footage from a congressional source. FILE - In this Oct. 8, 2015, file photo, Rep. Jason Chaffetz,... WASHINGTON (AP) — A trade group for abortion providers is asking a top House Republican to investigate after secretly recorded videos were posted online by a conservative blogger who wrote that he got the footage from a congressional source. A trade group for abortion providers is asking Chaffetz to investigate after secretly recorded videos were posted online by a conservative blogger who wrote that he got the footage from a congressional source. WASHINGTON (AP) — A trade group for abortion providers is asking a top House Republican to investigate after secretly recorded videos were posted online by a conservative blogger who wrote that he got the footage from a congressional source.
